# Accessibility

- Semantic HTML first: `<section>`, `<article>`, real headings, real links.
  ARIA only where semantics cannot express the relationship.
- Heading levels must be configurable (`heading-level` attribute) and nest
  correctly in any host page.
- Visible focus: `:focus-visible` ring meeting WCAG AA contrast.
- Full keyboard operability: every card reachable and activatable via
  keyboard, logical tab order, no focus traps.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (disable transitions/transforms) and
  `prefers-contrast`.
- Colour contrast AA minimum for all text and interactive states.
- Decorative media: `alt=""`/`aria-hidden="true"`. Meaningful media: real alt
  text sourced from data.
- Any change to rendered markup must keep the axe-core a11y test at **zero
  violations**.
